From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 16:59:50 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 06/12] drm/msm/dpu: Reassert core clock rate on runtime resume

DPU runtime suspend can drop the power-domain performance state even
though the clock framework still reports the previously programmed core
clock rate after the clocks are enabled again. In that case the DPU perf
code may not call dev_pm_opp_set_rate() before the hardware state is
restored, leaving the clock rate and the OPP required-opps vote out of
sync.

This can make high bandwidth modes fail after system suspend/resume. On
SC8280XP, a 4k120 mode can resume with the DP link trained successfully,
but later hit CTL recovery and vblank timeouts because the MMCX
performance state was not reasserted before DPU register programming.

Reapply the current DPU core clock rate during runtime resume, after
enabling the clocks and before restoring VBIF and encoder state. This
makes the OPP framework restore the required-opps vote without forcing a
higher clock rate than the one already selected.

Fixes: b0530eb11913 ("drm/msm/dpu: Use OPP API to set clk/perf state")
Signed-off-by: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
(cherry picked from commit 228e6a0642cf3ec83907dce3d84af02f7bb2577c)
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_kms.c | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_kms.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_kms.c
index 35f7af4743d7..fc3a65385b19 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_kms.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_kms.c
@@ -1454,6 +1454,7 @@ static int __maybe_unused dpu_runtime_resume(struct device *dev)
 	struct dpu_kms *dpu_kms = to_dpu_kms(priv->kms);
 	struct drm_encoder *encoder;
 	struct drm_device *ddev;
+	unsigned long core_rate;
 
 	ddev = dpu_kms->dev;
 
@@ -1463,6 +1464,24 @@ static int __maybe_unused dpu_runtime_resume(struct device *dev)
 		return rc;
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * Runtime suspend can drop the power-domain performance state even when
+	 * the clock framework still reports the previously programmed rate.
+	 * Re-assert the current core clock rate so OPP required-opps are restored
+	 * before touching DPU registers.
+	 */
+	core_rate = dpu_kms_get_clk_rate(dpu_kms, "core");
+	if (core_rate) {
+		core_rate = min_t(unsigned long, core_rate, dpu_kms->perf.max_core_clk_rate);
+		rc = dev_pm_opp_set_rate(&dpu_kms->pdev->dev, core_rate);
+		if (rc) {
+			DPU_ERROR("failed to restore core clock rate %lu: %d\n",
+				  core_rate, rc);
+			return rc;
+		}
+		dpu_kms->perf.core_clk_rate = core_rate;
+	}
+
 	dpu_vbif_init_memtypes(dpu_kms);
 
 	drm_for_each_encoder(encoder, ddev)
